# Draft:List of Best Results on Ninja Warrior (women)

Definitions
Best Female Result
The competitor(s) who cleared the most obstacles in the season. Ties are not broken based on distance within an obstacle.
Last Woman Standing (Golden Competitor)
The single competitor who was awarded the title of Last Woman Standing for having the best overall performance. In VS competitions, these rules are used to determine the winner of each heat. In Japan, this is referred to as Golden Competitor. Determination is based on the following conditions, in order:
# If the course was completed, fastest completion time.
# Farthest obstacle reached.
# Failure state (a timeout beats a failure).
# If the stage is the Final Stage, time to reach the buzzer.
# If the stage is the Final Stage, distance reached.
# Time elapsed when the failed obstacle was started, if the time is shown.
# If the obstacle is the first obstacle of the 2nd or 3rd Stage, the completion time of the prior stage.
# If the obstacle is the first obstacle of the 1st Stage, or of a head to head heat, the individual who spent the least time on the course.
# If a discernable and meaningful difference in progress within the obstacle is possible, that will be used.
# If the obstacle is the first obstacle of the 1st Stage, and not all runs were shown in full, no competitor will be considered Last Woman Standing.
# If the competitors failed the same obstacle and the time is either unavailable or too close to call, it will be considered a tie.
Last Woman Standing (Japan)
The competitor who was shown running last during the broadcast, regardless of if they earned Best Result. In all but  cases, the Last Woman Standing also achieved best result.
Total Victory
The competitor(s) who cleared all four stages under the traditional Survival Attack rules.
Champion
The sole competitor who was declared Last Woman Standing in any season that guarantees a winner through an untimed final.
Most Valuable Player
In International VS competitions, the competitor with the most clears and points contributed in the least time.
List of Best Results
All results are taken from their respective broadcasts. Season acronyms are based on the abbreviations seen here. All competitors are assumed to be the nationality of the corresponding show except where indicated with a flag.
:   Indicates that the competitor was not named Last Man Standing, but was Golden Competitor (Limited to Japan).
:   LWS exceptions: indicates the competitor who was declared Last Man Standing did not achieve a best result. See Last Woman Standing exceptions.
